<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>1) What kind of caster is a Shammy or BL? Int? Wis?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Shammies and BL's are both WIS casters. As I'm sure you've figured out, a BL is kind of like &quot;Shammy Lite&quot; when it comes to spells. In some ways they are remind me of a pally to a cleric or a SK to a necro. A BL to me is sort of like a monk meets a shammy plus something totally new.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> 2) Are there any ways to permanently boost the stats associated with casting spells with this or other classes, or is it all about spell and item buffs? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Not completely sure what you're asking with this one, so let's cover a few areas:<br>
<br>
Base stats (STR/WIS etc) can only be adjusted via either equipment (for example, a Acrylia Studded Cloak at something like +7 WIS) or via AA points (Inherent WIS). Characters routinely get to the 60- maximum of 255 using various gear. For example, I'm fairly sure that Ursi has a 255 WIS unbuffed, and I know that Plax does. My Cleric runs around 170 WIS unbuffed, even though her WIS at birth (or when she's naked) is only something like 124.<br>
<br>
Equipment can also add to mana (essentially giving you a bigger mana pool and more casts before you are OOM) and hit points directly.<br>
<br>
So, I *think* the answer to your question is that, other than the AA option, it is &quot;all about spell and item buffs&quot;. Obviously, item &quot;buffs&quot; are generally &gt; spell buffs because they are essentially permanent (unless you chose to take them off or die and are naked).<br>
<br>
One other item note: Focus Items. While these don't change your base stats, they can increase effectiveness. Some increase the length of a buff or a dot (indirectly saving mana by lengthening time before recast), others save regents or directly decrease mana use (healing efficiency II for example saves you 25% on healing related spells that are level 44 or below).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>3) Which spells and items would reap the most benefits? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I don't know BL's well enough to answer this. There are lots of great WIS caster items out there (for example, Velium Jasper rings run around 350pp and add like +6 to WIS each), but, as a BL, you probably want to consider the melee aspect too, so may not want to give up everything to WIS on rings when you could have something like a AC6 +65HP ring or something that adds STR (and therfore ups attack and damage).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>4) Is there a preferred resource with this information, or are you using lore knowledge?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
This is from lore I would say. That said, a lot of my &quot;lore&quot; comes from places like allakhazams, caster's realm, and usenet. There are shammy specific sites, and you can often see great discussions on things like mana calculation on some of the larger guild websites or server sites for servers other than Povar (Povar does not have a decent server specific website IMHO).<br>
<br>
Hope this helps!<br>
