<br>
Basically I'm getting the whole cycle down, and it works like this:<br>
<br>
If I'm pulling, I tell my pet to sit just in front of the group, then go hunting for mobs. Otherwise I just wait for the puller. I /assist the puller then send the pet in to stop the targeted mob a few steps away from the group. Pet takes some damage while everyone gets situated and starts their nukes, slows, etc. I've found that casting Ice Spear will always pop that mob free of the pet and pull it to me quite often. We had a 32 Mage in our group so I'm figuring if I can keep agro off him, it should work alright in most cases.<br>
<br>
BTW, I'm hunting a lot in The Overthere near the SkyFire Mountains zone line. Kinda slow, but very reliable. And of course, Avoid Dragoons, cos they suck hardcore.<br>
<br>
